 Tracey began her career in 1993 and joined Goldberg & de Villiers in 2005. She took up the position of Director a year later. Tracey studied at Nelson Mandela University and was admitted as an attorney in 1995, a conveyancer in 1995, and a notary public in 1997. Her areas of expertise include Property law, Conveyancing, Commercial contracts, Notarial work and Trusts. Tracey serves as a member of the Cape Law Society as well as the South Eastern Cape Attorneys Association For professional legal advice, Tracey can be contacted on Direct telephone: +27 (0)41 501 9807/53 E-mail: twg@goldlaw.co.za; Visit:Â www.goldbergdevilliers.co.za 